name: 4-hydroxy-tetrahydrodipicolinate reductase
classes: Acting on CH or CH2 groups;
With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
comment: Studies [2] of the enzyme from the bacterium Escherichia coli have shown that the enzyme accepts (2S,4S)-4-hydroxy-2,3,4,5-tetrahydrodipicolinate and not (S)-2,3-dihydrodipicolinate as originally thought [1].

references.title: The reduction step in diaminopimelic acid biosynthesis.
NMR studies uncover alternate substrates for dihydrodipicolinate synthase and suggest that dihydrodipicolinate reductase is also a dehydratase.
